ssinsider.com%2Ftiktok-popular-lip-stain-review-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok-popular%20lip%20stain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20initially%20goes%20on%20as%20a%20dark%2C%20iridescent%20royal%20blue.%20You%20leave%20the%20stain%20on%20your%20lips%20for%2010-30%20seconds%20and%20then%20wipe%20it%20away%20with%20a%20damp%20cloth%20to%20reveal%20the%20true%20color%20underneath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20really%20appreciate%20about%20this%20product%20is%20that%20the%20applicator%20has%20a%20thin%20edge%2C%20which%20means%20I%20can%20use%20it%20to%20line%20my%20lips%20first%20before%20filling%20them%20in.%20The%20longer%20you%20leave%20the%20stain%20on%20before%20wiping%20it%20away%2C%20the%20deeper%20the%20pigment.%20I%20like%20that%20I%20can%20leave%20it%20on%20for%2010%20seconds%20if%20I%20want%20a%20more%20muted%20look%20or%20leave%20it%20on%20for%20a%20full%2030%20seconds%20to%20get%20a%20more%20intense%20color%20payoff.%20Another%20huge%20advantage%20here%20is%20that%20there%20are%2018%20different%20color%20options%20%E2%80%94%20I%20opted%20for%20%26quot%3BWhimsical%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20that%20perfect%20my-lips-but-better%20rosy%20shade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20stain%20lasted%20a%20full%20six%20hours%2C%20making%20it%20the%20longest-lasting%20one%20I%20tried.%20Even%20after%20I%20applied%20a%20lip%20balm%20or%20gloss%20on%20top%2C%20it%20didn't%20fade%20or%20run%2C%20which%20is%20pretty%20impressive.%20That%20said%2C%20this%20one%20did%20seem%20to%20fade%20pretty%20unevenly%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20if%20I%20didn't%20add%20that%20extra%20layer%20of%20balm%20or%20gloss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20buildable%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side%20by%20side%20image%20of%20the%20author%20wearing%20the%20Benefit%20Cosmetics%20Benetint%20Liquid%20Lip%20%2B%20Cheek%20Blush%20Stain%20upon%20first%20application%20and%20after%20wearing%20it%20for%20hours.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6e5c5c6ad288d147dbb71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Strong%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBenetint%20is%20largely%20considered%20the%20OG%20lip%20stain%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20actually%20the%20first%20product%20Benefit%20Cosmetics%20introduced.%20But%20here's%20a%20fun%20fact%20for%20you%3A%20It%20was%20originally%20sold%20as%20a%20nipple%20tint%20for%20exotic%20dancers%20back%20in%201976%20when%20it%20launched.%20It's%20since%20been%20renamed%20and%20reformulated%2C%20and%20the%20brand%20has%20added%20a%20small%20handful%20of%20new%20color%20options%20as%20well.%20I%20decided%20to%20try%20Floratint%2C%20which%20Benefit%20describes%20as%20a%20desert%20rose%2C%20but%20I%20found%20it%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20a%20bright%20coral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20formula%20is%20definitely%20a%20lot%20thinner%20and%20more%20watery%20than%20other%20tints.%20It%20dries%20down%20to%20a%20matte%20finish%2C%20and%20once%20it%20sets%2C%20it's%20pretty%20tough%20to%20get%20off%2C%20so%20I%20learned%20to%20fix%20any%20mess-ups%20quickly.%20This%20one%20didn't%20feel%20super%20drying%20on%20my%20lips%2C%20but%20it%20also%20doesn't%20contain%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20other%20ultra-nourishing%20ingredients%20that%20other%20stains%20on%20this%20list%20feature%2C%20so%20I%20did%20find%20myself%20yearning%20to%20layer%20it%20with%20a%20balm.%20If%20you%20like%20that%20just-ate-a-popsicle%20look%2C%20this%20stain%20is%20definitely%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20far%2C%20the%20biggest%20perk%20with%20this%20stain%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20it's%20pretty%20buildable.%20One%20coat%20leaves%20a%20sheer%20wash%20of%20color%2C%20while%20two%20or%20three%20coats%20provide%20a%20richer%20and%20more%20vibrant%20pop%20of%20pigment.%20It's%20a%20multitasking%20product%2C%20too%3A%20Reviewers%20say%20they%20also%20use%20it%20as%20a%20blush%20or%20staining%20lip%20liner%2C%20although%20I%20haven't%20yet%20tried%20to%20apply%20it%20either%20of%20those%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMost%20moisturizing%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side%20by%20side%20image%20of%20the%20author%20wearing%20the%20Hard%20Candy%20Pop%20Tint%20Lip%20Stain%20upon%20first%20application%20and%20after%20wearing%20it%20for%20hours.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6e804a466d2b74ab2bdfe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Strong%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20first%20spotted%20this%20budget-friendly%20stain%20on%20BeautyTok%2C%20where%20I%20saw%20countless%20influencers%20raving%20about%20the%20dewy%20finish%20and%20impressive%20color%20payoff.%20They%20weren't%20wrong.%20This%20one%20felt%20incredibly%20moisturizing%20thanks%20to%20ingredients%20like%20hyaluronic%20acid%2C%20jojoba%20oil%2C%20and%20squalane%20in%20the%20formula%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20also%20offered%20long-lasting%2C%20rich%20pigment.%20I'd%20certainly%20be%20adding%20more%20of%20these%20stains%20to%20my%20collection%20if%20there%20were%20more%20than%20four%20color%20options.%20I%20loved%20the%20wine-red%20shade%20I%20tried%3A%20%26quot%3BBerry%20Drops.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20observation%20after%20applying%20this%20stain%20is%20that%20it%20smells%20a%20bit%20like%20a%20cherry%20coughdrop%20%E2%80%94%20I%20happen%20to%20like%20the%20scent%2C%20which%20I%20imagine%20comes%20from%20the%20sweet%20cherry%20seed%20oil%20in%20the%20formula.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20doe-foot%20applicator%20on%20this%20one%20is%20a%20tad%20larger%2C%20making%20it%20a%20bit%20more%20tricky%20to%20apply%20with%20precision%2C%20but%20the%20angled%20shape%20definitely%20helps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20lip%20balms%20will%20be%20chock-full%20of%20nourishing%2C%20moisturizing%20ingredients%20and%20devoid%20of%20potential%20irritants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-ingredients-for-lip-balm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20ingredients%20for%20lip%20balm%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELanolin%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPetroleum%20jelly%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShea%20butter%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECocoa%20butter%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EVitamin%20E%20(tocopherol)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECastor%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Academy%20of%20Dermatology%20(AAD)%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aad.org%2Fpublic%2Feveryday-care%2Fskin-care-basics%2Fdry%2Fheal-dry-chapped-lips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvises%20looking%20for%20lip%20balms%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20contain%20at%20least%20one%20of%20the%20aforementioned%20healing%20ingredients%2C%20along%20with%20ceramides%2C%20if%20you're%20dealing%20with%20dry%2C%20chapped%20lips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEspecially%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20or%20if%20you%20spend%20time%20outdoors%2C%20the%20AAD%20recommends%20getting%20a%20lip%20balm%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aad.org%2Fpublic%2Feveryday-care%2Fskin-care-basics%2Fdry%2Fheal-dry-chapped-lips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtaining%20at%20least%20SPF%2030%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20lip%20balms%20block%20out%20harmful%20UV%20rays%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20your%20lips%20to%20chap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20some%20common%20ingredients%20like%20menthol%2C%20phenol%2C%20and%20salicylic%20acid%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.clevelandclinic.org%2F6-signs-your-lip-balm-use-is-just-a-bad-habit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edry%20out%20the%20skin%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20AAD%2C%20preservatives%20(like%20parabens)%2C%20exfoliants%2C%20chemical%20sunscreens%2C%20and%20artificial%20colors%20and%20dyes%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommunity.aafa.org%2Fdb%2Fask-the-allergist%2Frecord%2Fdid-i-develop-an-allergy-to-the-ingredients-in-my-lip-balm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecause%20irritation%20or%20an%20allergic%20reaction%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20AAD%20recommends%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aad.org%2Fpublic%2Feveryday-care%2Fskin-care-basics%2Fdry%2Fheal-dry-chapped-lips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoiding%20the%20following%20ingredients%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20your%20lips%20are%20chapped%20so%20they%20can%20heal%20properly%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMenthol%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPhenol%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESalicylic%20acid%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECamphor%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEucalyptus%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFragrances%20and%20flavorings%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPropyl%20gallate%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EColor%20and%20finish%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELip%20balms%20come%20in%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20finishes%2C%20from%20matte%20and%20demi-matte%20(satin)%20to%20subtle%20shine%20and%20ultra-glossy.%20Matte%20and%20demi-matte%20finishes%20will%20look%20closer%20to%20classic%20chapstick.%20If%20you%20want%20your%20lip%20balm%20to%20do%20double%20duty%20as%20a%20gloss%20or%20use%20it%20to%20give%20matte%20lipsticks%20and%20lip%20stains%20a%20glossy%20finish%2C%20that's%20something%20to%20consider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETinted%20lip%20balms%20have%20some%20level%20of%20pigment%20in%20them%20to%20give%20your%20lips%20a%20hint%20of%20color.%20Typically%2C%20with%20lip%20balm%2C%20it's%20a%20pretty%20sheer%20tint%20that%20you%20can%20build%20with%20more%20layers%20for%20intensity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20lip%20balms%20are%20also%20scented%20or%20flavored.%20If%20you're%20picky%20about%20fragrances%2C%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20ingredients%20when%20shopping%20for%20lip%20balm%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20it's%20applied%20right%20near%20your%20nose%2C%20so%20you'll%20be%20smelling%20it%20all%20day%20and%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20sensitive%20skin%2C%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20some%20synthetic%20fragrances%20and%20added%20flavorings%20can%20cause%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommunity.aafa.org%2Fdb%2Fask-the-allergist%2Frecord%2Fdid-i-develop-an-allergy-to-the-ingredients-in-my-lip-balm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20allergic%20contact%20dermatitis%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20symptoms%20of%20which%20include%20redness%2C%20cracking%2C%20burning%2C%20itching%2C%20and%20a%20dry%20rash.%20This%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.clevelandclinic.org%2F6-signs-your-lip-balm-use-is-just-a-bad-habit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrue%20for%20artificial%20colors%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well.%20According%20to%20the%20AAD%2C%20citrus%2C%20cinnamon%2C%20and%20mint%2Fpeppermint%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aad.org%2Fpublic%2Feveryday-care%2Fskin-care-basics%2Fdry%2Fheal-dry-chapped-lips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20be%20particularly%20irritating%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20your%20lips%20are%20already%20dry%20or%20chapped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPackaging%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPackaging%20can%20make%20or%20break%20the%20lip%20balm%20experience.%20If%20it's%20difficult%20to%20apply%2C%20you%20probably%20won't%20find%20yourself%20wanting%20to%20use%20it%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20how%20fabulous%20the%20formula%20is.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20lip%20balms%20come%20in%20a%20pot.%20These%20either%20include%20a%20spatula%20for%20application%20or%20require%20you%20to%20use%20your%20fingers.%20Others%20come%20in%20a%20tube%20you%20can%20twist%20or%20squeeze%20to%20apply%20the%20product%20directly%20on%20your%20lips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIdeally%2C%20you'll%20probably%20want%20to%20find%20a%20lip%20balm%20that's%20easy%20to%20use%20on%20the%20go%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20use%20your%20hands%20to%20apply%20it%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20work%20very%20hard%20to%20get%20the%20product%20out%20of%20the%20packaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFAQs%3Ch3%3EWhat%20does%20lip%20balm%20do%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EExposing%20our%20lips%20to%20cold%20air%20and%20the%20sun%20and%20even%20neglecting%20to%20drink%20enough%20water%20or%20licking%20them%20too%20often%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F22005-chapped-lips%23management-and-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecause%20them%20to%20become%20chapped%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dry%2C%20and%20flakey.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F22005-chapped-lips%23management-and-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20shown%20that%20your%20lips%20actually%20have%20a%20weak%20skin%20barrier%20and%20aren't%20able%20to%20retain%20water%20as%20well%20as%20the%20skin%20on%20other%20parts%20of%20your%20body.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20but%20the%20skin%20on%20our%20lips%20doesn't%20contain%20any%20oil%20or%20sweat%20glands%2C%20making%20it%20even%20more%20prone%20to%20dryness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20lip%20balm%20comes%20in%3A%20it%20can%20often%20help%20either%20by%20outright%20healing%20cracks%20in%20the%20skin%20or%20simply%20by%20hydrating%20them%20and%20protecting%20them%20from%20moisture%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20it%20better%20to%20put%20lip%20balm%20on%20wet%20or%20dry%20lips%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20advise%20applying%20lip%20balm%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcgill.ca%2Foss%2Farticle%2Fdid-you-know%2Fdid-you-know-you-should-apply-lip-balm-your-lips-get-chapped%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSo%2520if%2520you%2520really%2520want%2Cto%2520lock%2520in%2520extra%2520moisture.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eright%20after%20you%20shower%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20hot%20shower%20can%20create%20a%20humid%2C%20moisture-rich%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20but%20as%20soon%20as%20you%20step%20out%2C%20the%20water%20in%20the%20upper%20layers%20of%20your%20skin%20evaporates%2C%20making%20your%20lips%20more%20prone%20to%20dryness.%20Lip%20balms%20contain%20beeswax%2C%20shea%20butter%2C%20and%20other%20substances%20that%20form%20a%20protective%20barrier%20on%20your%20skin%2C%20preventing%20that%20moisture%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there%20isn't%20a%20lot%20of%20research%20yet%20on%20whether%20it's%20better%20to%20put%20lip%20balm%20on%20wet%20or%20dry%20lips%20%E2%80%94%20so%20you%20can%20feel%20free%20to%20do%20whatever%20feels%20best%20for%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20using%20too%20much%20lip%20balm%20bad%20for%20you%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20bust%20a%20common%20myth%3A%20regularly%20using%20lip%20balm%20won't%20generally%20make%20your%20lips%20more%20chapped%20or%20cause%20your%20body%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.clevelandclinic.org%2F6-signs-your-lip-balm-use-is-just-a-bad-habit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estop%20supplying%20the%20lips%20with%20natural%20moisture%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegularly%20applying%20lip%20balm%20shouldn't%20have%20any%20negative%20consequences%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20choose%20the%20right%20one%2C%20that%20is.%20As%20long%20as%20you%20avoid%20potentially%20drying%20or%20irritating%20ingredients%2C%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20apply%20lip%20balm%20multiple%20times%20daily%20with%20no%20negative%20effects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20lip%20balm%20ever%20causes%20burning%20or%20stinging%2C%20the%20AAD%20recommends%20you%20stop%20using%20it%20immediately%20%E2%80%94%20those%20are%20signs%20of%20irritation%2C%20which%20could%20worsen%20the%20condition%20of%20